translated: Huberth, Gustaf Elis, Lieutenant Colonel, Skövde, b. July 29, 1896 in Ringarum, Östergötland. Married Irma Gunilfla Nordlander in 1929. Children: Sven b. 1943, Gunilla b. 1946. He completed his high school education in 1916, received his officer training in 1919, attended the General Course at the Military Academy from 1925-1928, the Staff Course from 1928-1930, and completed his Gymnastics Director education in 1928 and his Intelligence Course in 1932. He served in England in 1937 and in Germany in 1939. He was a Second Lieutenant in the Västern Regiment in 1919, a Lieutenant in 1924, a Lieutenant of the Intelligence Corps in 1933, a Captain in 1934, and a Lieutenant Colonel of the Intelligence Corps in 1947. He served in the Northern Cavalry Regiment from 1933-1937, was employed by the Army Supply from 1937-1942, was the Commander of the First Intelligence Company from 1942-1945, and was a teacher at the Intelligence School from 1939-1945. He was also a staff instructor for III. Military District Staff in Skövde from 1945. He owns farms in Grönstorp and Skinnebo in Östergötland and Kalm. He enjoys motorsport and has been awarded the Royal Order of the Sword and the Shooting Medal.
